HEADWORD: Menhir
<hw>Men"hir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. Armor.
<ets>men</ets> stone + <ets>hir</ets> high.]</ety> <def>A large stone
set upright in olden times as a memorial or monument. Many, of unknown
date, are found in Brittany and throughout Northern Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

